    description: "S4Proof CC 70 is a high-performance, cement-based, single-component waterproofing material that works through crystallization. It is designed for both positive and negative hydrostatic pressure applications. By penetrating into the concrete and forming insoluble minerals in capillary spaces, it effectively blocks water pathways, providing long-lasting water resistance. This product is ideal for waterproofing foundations, basement walls, retaining walls, and other concrete structures exposed to water pressure. S4Proof CC 70 is easy to apply and can be used on both new and old concrete surfaces. ✅ Advantages: Easy to apply without mixing, requiring no primer Forms insoluble crystals that block water pathways Provides long-lasting water impermeability Can be applied on both new and old concrete surfaces Effective under both positive and negative hydrostatic pressure Resistant to water penetration, freeze-thaw cycles, and environmental factors 📌 Application Areas: Waterproofing for foundations, retaining walls, and basement walls Applications under positive and negative hydrostatic pressure Used in water tanks, swimming pools, underground garages, and tunnels Suitable for dams, concrete pipes, irrigation canals, and culverts Waterproofing under curtain wall concretes ⚙️ Technical Specifications: Property Value Chemical Structure Cement-based, polymer-enhanced powder Density ~1.60 g/cm³ (±0.1) Mixture Ratio 7.00-7.50 L water / 25 kg powder Mortar Density 1.90-2.10 g/cm³ (±0.1) Pot Life 30 minutes Working Time 20 minutes Full Curing Time 28 days Consumption 2.50-3.00 kg/m² (for 2 mm thickness) 🛠️ Application Instructions: Ensure the surface is clean, smooth, and solid, and free from dust, oil, grease, and other contaminants. Mix 7-7.5 liters of water per 25 kg of powder until a smooth, lump-free mixture is obtained. Allow the mixture to rest for 3-5 minutes and then remix for 30 seconds before use. Apply the mixed material in at least 2 coats with a brush or trowel. Each layer should be applied perpendicular to the previous layer. Allow at least 6-12 hours drying time between coats. If more than 12 hours pass between coats, re-moisten the surface before applying the next layer. ⚠️ Warnings: Do not apply in temperatures below +5°C or above +30°C. Avoid applying during rainy or windy weather conditions, or in areas at risk of freezing. Ensure the surface is free from moisture before application. Not suitable for use on surfaces such as wood, metal, fiberboard, or plaster. 🧽 Cleaning & Storage: Clean tools immediately after use with clean water. Store in its original packaging in a dry, cool, and frost-free environment. Shelf life is 12 months when stored under appropriate conditions. 🧯 Safety: Wear protective clothing, gloves, and masks during application. Avoid contact with eyes and skin. In case of contact, rinse immediately with water and seek medical attention if necessary. Keep out of reach of children. Consult the Safety Data Sheet (SDS) for further safety precautions.",
